  "text": "Found 3 Java source files in apache/kafka that define ACL authorization logic under clients/src/main/. No matching files found in core/src/main/java (only a Scala file core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/AclApis.scala exists, which is outside the Java scope). The three files are: (1) Authorizer.java defines the public interface Authorizer, which is the pluggable authorizer interface for Kafka brokers that extends Configurable and Closeable. This interface defines methods for authorization (authorize), ACL creation (createAcls), ACL deletion (deleteAcls), and ACL queries (acls). (2) AuthorizerServerInfo.java defines the public interface AuthorizerServerInfo, which provides runtime broker configuration metadata to authorizers during startup, including cluster resource, broker id, endpoints, inter-broker endpoint, and early start listeners. (3) AuthorizerNotReadyException.java defines the public exception class AuthorizerNotReadyException, which extends RetriableException and indicates that the authorizer is not ready to receive requests yet. These three files represent the core interfaces and exceptions for ACL authorization logic in the Kafka broker."
}

